title: 4 Stocks To Watch  AVXL  BSQR  ERII  NEO
content:
The market had a wonderful day on Monday  It was strong  and a lot of biotechs led the way  We re going to take a look at a mixture of stocks  including biotech stocks that are acting very well  There are some swing trades as well 
Anavex Life Sciences Corp   OTC AVXLD  is a monster and really is acting great  It s extremely speculative  and trading thin  The fifth wave is under way  which could get it up to 20  give or take a point or two  Maybe  We re not sure yet  Monday was spectacular as it ran up 2 42 to 13 00  the high for the day  or 22 8   on 4 million shares  the most volume it s had for a while  It did trade 4 7 million shares back in July when it broke out  That was a strong day for this stock 
BSQUARE Corp   O BSQR   one of our swing trades  is acting great  It s moving up a little at a time  pausing a day or two between each move  and on Monday  it was up another 67 cents to 11 55  or 6   on 345 200 shares traded  Not huge volume  but when it gets up near 14  it may trade some pretty heavy volume  For now  stay long 
Energy Recovery  Inc   O ERII  had a significant day on Monday because of the wedge that was forming after the big  explosive gap up  It was up 60 cents to 7 77  or 8 37   on 2 2 million shares  The spike high was at 8 16  and Monday s high is 7 99  If it gets through that level  it could run up to 10 10 plus 
Neogenomics Inc   O NEO  is acting well  It exploded on Monday  up 95 cents to 8 00  or 13 5   on 2 5 million shares  That s another example of a breakaway move  It formed a beautiful bull wedge  Low volume ebb  and then boom  it ran  It appears to be heading up toward the 9 1 4 1 2 zone 
Other stocks on the long side include A10 Networks  Inc   N ATEN   Cellectis S A   O CLLS   Concert Pharmaceuticals  Inc   O CNCE   Cytokinetics  Incorporated  O CYTK   Five Prime Therapeutics  Inc   O FPRX   JinkoSolar Holding Co   Ltd   N JKS   Juno Therapeutics Inc   O JUNO   Neurocrine Biosciences Inc   O NBIX   Natural Health Trends Corp   O NHTC   and Steel Dynamics Inc   O STLD

title: U S  stocks mixed at close of trade  Dow Jones Industrial Average up 0 11
content:
Investing com   U S  stocks were mixed after the close on Friday  as gains in the Utilities  Consumer Services and Basic Materials sectors led shares higher while losses in the Financials  Technology and Industrials sectors led shares lower 
At the close in New York  the Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 0 11  to hit a new 1 month high  while the S P 500 index climbed 0 08   and the NASDAQ Composite index fell 0 05  
The best performers of the session on the Dow Jones Industrial Average were Cisco Systems Inc  NASDAQ CSCO   which rose 1 72  or 0 50 points to trade at 29 55 at the close  Meanwhile  Nike Inc  NYSE NKE  added 1 49  or 1 54 points to end at 104 98 and Home Depot Inc  NYSE HD  was up 1 26  or 1 41 points to 113 35 in late trade 
The worst performers of the session were Microsoft Corporation  NASDAQ MSFT   which fell 0 87  or 0 42 points to trade at 48 30 at the close  Boeing Company  NYSE BA  declined 0 73  or 1 08 points to end at 146 88 and American Express Company  NYSE AXP  was down 0 66  or 0 53 points to 80 22 
The top performers on the S P 500 were PEPCO Holdings Inc  NYSE POM  which rose 8 83  to 27 00  Bed Bath   Beyond Inc  NASDAQ BBBY  which was up 5 31  to settle at 73 35 and Macy s Inc  NYSE M  which gained 5 24  to close at 66 53 
The worst performers were Keurig Green Mountain Inc  NASDAQ GMCR  which was down 8 55  to 94 26 in late trade  Symantec Corporation  NASDAQ SYMC  which lost 5 48  to settle at 24 48 and Navient Cor  NASDAQ NAVI  which was down 3 38  to 19 16 at the close 
The top performers on the NASDAQ Composite were MagneGas Corporation  NASDAQ MNGA  which rose 59 34  to 1 450  BSQUARE Corporation  NASDAQ BSQR  which was up 34 47  to settle at 5 500 and Interphase Corporation  NASDAQ INPH  which gained 21 98  to close at 0 61 
The worst performers were Joes Jeans Inc  NASDAQ JOEZ  which was down 28 18  to 0 110 in late trade  Local Corporation  NASDAQ LOCM  which lost 27 29  to settle at 0 400 and RMG Networks Holding Corp  NASDAQ RMGN  which was down 26 90  to 1 060 at the close 
Rising stocks outnumbered declining ones on the New York Stock Exchange by 1732 to 1396 and 3 ended unchanged  on the Nasdaq Stock Exchange  1450 fell and 1340 advanced  while 5 ended unchanged 
Shares in Keurig Green Mountain Inc  NASDAQ GMCR  fell to 52 week lows  losing 8 55  or 8 81 to 94 26  Shares in Nike Inc  NYSE NKE  rose to all time highs  gaining 1 49  or 1 54 to 104 98  Shares in BSQUARE Corporation  NASDAQ BSQR  rose to 3 years highs  gaining 34 47  or 1 410 to 5 500  Shares in Local Corporation  NASDAQ LOCM  fell to all time lows  down 27 29  or 0 150 to 0 400  
The CBOE Volatility Index  which measures the implied volatility of S P 500 options  was down 2 83  to 12 38 
Gold for June delivery was down 0 07  or 0 90 to  1224 30 a troy ounce  Elsewhere in commodities trading  Crude oil for delivery in June fell 0 02  or 0 01 to hit  59 87 a barrel  while the July Brent oil contract rose 0 32  or 0 21 to trade at  66 92 a barrel 
EUR USD was up 0 31  to 1 1444  while USD JPY rose 0 16  to 119 35 
The US Dollar Index was down 0 09  at 93 32

title: 4 Stocks To Watch Today  GLOB  OPK  SGEN  TTPH
content:
The markets had a very volatile session on Wednesday  the FOMC announcement regarding rates  one minute it s up  the next it was down  with a mixed close  There s a lot of stocks that we follow here that are doing well  A couple of them had a real big day on Wednesday  Let s take a look at them 
Globant SA  NYSE GLOB  broke out twice since late April  pulled back in a multi week falling wedge to the trendline  popped to resistance  backed off  and was up 2 44 to 26 01  or 10 3   on 235 200 shares traded  The volume was low  although it was big for this stock  It broke out across the double top on Wednesday  and the next target for GLOB is 31 
Opko Health Inc  NYSE OPK  continues to look great  It has stair stepped its way higher 8 consecutive days  punching through resistance level at mid channel  On Wednesday  it was up 67 cents to 18 02  or nearly 4   on 5 1 million shares  Going forward the targets are 20  and then 22 
Seattle Genetics Inc  NASDAQ SGEN  hasn t done anything for a long time  but it started to move  forming a left shoulder head right shoulder  an inverse head and shoulders  then it broke out  and on Wednesday  it was up 1 76 to 42 99  or 4 2   on 1 6 million shares  If it continues upward  the targets are 45  and then 49 1 2 going forward 
Tetraphase Pharmaceuticals Inc  NASDAQ TTPH  had an excellent day on Wednesday  up 4 84 to 45 33  or 12   on 1 3 million shares  It broke out of a key congestion range  which it s been in since late December  It consolidated after a huge run up from the 8 range all the way up to the 40 s  which is an indication that it wants to go higher  The swing target is in the 60 65 range 
Other stocks on Harry s Charts of the Day included BSQUARE Corporation  NASDAQ BSQR   Cablevision Systems Corporation  NYSE CVC   Cynosure Inc  NASDAQ CYNO   Dycom Industries Inc  NYSE DY   Prima Biomed Ltd  NASDAQ PBMD   IsoRay Inc  NYSE ISR   Momo Inc  NASDAQ MOMO   Pep Boys Manny Moe   Jack  NYSE PBY   Shake Shack Inc   NYSE SHAK   Sarepta Therapeutics Inc  NASDAQ SRPT   and 500 Com Ltd  NYSE WBAI
